# VetPlant UI/UX Screen Generation

- Design both breakpoints for each screen: desktop (`1280px+`) and mobile (`375px`).
- Use VetPlant visual identity consistently: teal/green primary, neutral light backgrounds, dark readable text, warm accent colors only for emphasis.
- Keep unauthenticated flows with top navbar; authenticated flows with left sidebar.
- Registration/auth screens must use top navbar.
- Build cards with rounded corners (`8-12px`), subtle shadow, and clear spacing.
- Use outlined icon style and keep icon size/weight consistent.

## Form UX Rules

- Labels always above inputs; never placeholder-only fields.
- Required fields must display a red asterisk (`*`).
- Show helper text in muted gray when guidance is needed.
- Show inline validation under fields and keep error text red.
- For multi-step forms, show a persistent stepper:
  - desktop: labeled horizontal steps
  - mobile: compact dots + current step label
- Keep document upload with clear accepted formats and status badges.
- If the flow supports deferred docs, include a visible “skip and upload later” action.

## Layout and Quality Gate

- Prevent clipping/overlap: use fit-content layouts where needed and ensure all content is visible.
- Keep reusable components grouped in a dedicated “Reusable Components” area.
- Reuse existing components before creating new variants; avoid duplicates.
- Before finalizing, validate visuals and layout problems (no clipped or overlapping elements).
